article.headline: UC Davis 75, Cal Poly-SLO 73
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Vince Oliver had 19 points and nine rebounds, including the game-winning 3-pointer, as UC Davis rallied from a 14-point deficit to beat Cal Poly 75-73 Wednesday. Oliver's 3 came with five seconds left, and Cal Poly's Chaz Thomas missed both free throws after getting fouled with less than a second left. Cal Poly (6-17, 3-10 Big West) led 42-36 at halftime and opened the second half on a 14-6 run to take a 14-point lead with 14 minutes left. UC Davis (12-14, 7-6) rallied to within 11 with 8:42 left and tied the game at 69-69 after Kyle Brucculeri hit a 3 with 2:51 left. Cal Poly scored the next four points before consecutive 3s from Brucculeri and Oliver erased the deficit. Shawn Lewis led Cal Poly with 26 points and eight rebounds, and Lorenzo Keeler added 18 points.
